{"questionId":"9069889","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The equations for two acid-base reactions are given below.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">HCO<sub>3</sub><sup>–</sup> (aq) + H<sub>2</sub>O (l) <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" \\rightleftharpoons \">\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇌</mo>\n</math></span> H<sub>2</sub>CO<sub>3</sub> (aq) + OH<sup>–</sup> (aq)<br>HCO<sub>3</sub><sup>–</sup> (aq) + H<sub>2</sub>O (l) <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"&nbsp;\\rightleftharpoons \">\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇌</mo>\n</math></span> CO<sub>3</sub><sup>2–</sup> (aq) + H<sub>3</sub>O<sup>+</sup> (aq)</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Identify two different amphiprotic species in the above reactions.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>HCO<sub>3</sub><sup>–</sup> AND H<sub>2</sub>O</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9069889","referenceCode":"17N.2.sl.TZ0.b.i","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Identify two different amphiprotic species in the above reactions.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 8: Acids and bases","8.1 Theories of acids and bases","Core","Topic 8: Acids and bases"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}